<li id="cite_note-Tipler2003b-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Tipler2003b_31-0" title="">^</a></b> Frank Tipler, <a href="http://www.geocities.com/theophysics/tipler-omega-point-and-christianity.html" class="external text" title="http://www.geocities.com/theophysics/tipler-omega-point-and-christianity.html" rel="nofollow">"The Omega Point and Christianity,"</a> <i>Gamma</i>, Vol. 10, No. 2 (April 2003), pp. 14-23; note that the foregoing version corrects character formatting errors of the versions available <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20031113125255/http://home.worldonline.nl/~sttdc/tipler.htm" class="external text" title="http://web.archive.org/web/20031113125255/http://home.worldonline.nl/~sttdc/tipler.htm" rel="nofollow">here,</a> <a href="http://home.worldonline.nl/~sttdc/tipler.htm" class="external text" title="http://home.worldonline.nl/~sttdc/tipler.htm" rel="nofollow">here</a> and <a href="http://home.tiscali.nl/~sttdc/tipler.htm" class="external text" title="http://home.tiscali.nl/~sttdc/tipler.htm" rel="nofollow">here.</a> (Note: citation formatting in the above-quoted passage has been modified for clarity.) For the version in Dutch, see <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20040205030349/http://home.worldonline.nl/~sttdc/jrg10_nr2_p1423.htm" class="external text" title="http://web.archive.org/web/20040205030349/http://home.worldonline.nl/~sttdc/jrg10_nr2_p1423.htm" rel="nofollow">"Het Punt Omega en het christendom,"</a> <i>Gamma</i>, Jrg. 10, Nr. 2 (April 2003), pp. 14-23; also available <a href="http://home.tiscali.nl/~sttdc/jrg10_nr2_p1423.htm" class="external text" title="http://home.tiscali.nl/~sttdc/jrg10_nr2_p1423.htm" rel="nofollow">here.</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-Wilczek2002-32"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Wilczek2002_32-0" title="">^</a></b> Frank Wilczek, <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20020901123632/http://www.if.ufrgs.br/~jgallas/wilczek.html" class="external text" title="http://web.archive.org/web/20020901123632/http://www.if.ufrgs.br/~jgallas/wilczek.html" rel="nofollow">"Scaling Mount Planck III: Is That All There Is?,"</a> <i>Physics Today</i>, Vol. 55, Issue 8 (August 2002), pp. 10-11. See also <a href="http://www.physicstoday.org/pt/vol-55/iss-8/current.html" class="external text" title="http://www.physicstoday.org/pt/vol-55/iss-8/current.html" rel="nofollow">here</a> and <a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2002PhT....55h..10W" class="external text" title="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2002PhT....55h..10W" rel="nofollow">here.</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-33"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33" title="">^</a></b> Helen R. Quinn, <a href="http://www.slac.stanford.edu/cgi-wrap/getdoc/slac-pub-9258.ps.gz" class="external text" title="http://www.slac.stanford.edu/cgi-wrap/getdoc/slac-pub-9258.ps.gz" rel="nofollow">"The Asymmetry Between Matter and Antimatter,"</a> <i>Physics Today</i>, Vol. 56, Issue 2 (February 2003), pp. 30-35. See also <a href="http://www.physicstoday.org/pt/vol-56/iss-2/current.html" class="external text" title="http://www.physicstoday.org/pt/vol-56/iss-2/current.html" rel="nofollow">here</a> and <a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2003PhT....56b..30Q" class="external text" title="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2003PhT....56b..30Q" rel="nofollow">here.</a></li>
